step_data.thought:
I've successfully switched to the ÖPNVKarte layer, which is focused on public transportation networks. Looking at the current state of the page, I can see that the map is now displaying tiles from the ÖPNVKarte source (as indicated by the image URLs with 'tileserver.memomaps.de/tilegen' in them).

So far, I've explored two different map layers:
1. CyclOSM - A cycling-focused map style
2. ÖPNVKarte - A public transportation focused map style

There are still two other layers that I haven't tried yet:
1. Standard - The default OpenStreetMap style
2. Humanitarian - A style focused on humanitarian aid/disaster response

Let me switch to the Humanitarian layer next to see how it displays New York City. I need to click on the Humanitarian option [282] to switch to this layer.
